\date{2026-02-05}
\title{It's rude to show AI output to people.}
\author{liamoc}
\p{I came across [this article](https://distantprovince.by/posts/its-rude-to-show-ai-output-to-people/) by Alex Martsinovich which I thought captured very well one of the main objections I have to LLMs as a technology. It used to be that every piece of text, even down to a road sign, was written by a human somewhere with the intention of communicating something to you, the reader — what Alex calls "proof of thought". Thanks to LLMs, this fundamental property of language has been irrevocably destroyed: a massive tragedy in my view.  }